JSP Error Handeling
There are total two ways to handle exception in JSP page
1) By using JSP directive TAG <%@ page errorPage="error.jsp" %>  this will tell jsp if
 error occures in this page than go to /error.jsp
 
2) Using web.xml file and directly declaring it using xml tag by doing so we 
don't need to write above directive tag in each jsp page
<error-page>  
  <exception-type>java.lang.Exception</exception-type>  // this tells type of error like ArrayOutOfBound etc...
  <location>/error.jsp</location>  // when error will occur jsp will goto this page
 </error-page>  




